title: The Real Animated Adventures of Doc and Mharti
overview:
Justin actually made this as a way to poke fun at the idea of getting cease and desist letters. 

At the time (October 2006) he had nothing to lose and his original intention was to call this "back to the future: the new official universal studios cartoon featuring the new Doc Brown and Marty McFly" and then just sit back and wait for a letter from their lawyers to arrive. That's actually why it's so filthy. He was just looking to "troll" a big studio.

7 years later, hit new animated TV show on Hypothetical Network.

title: The Freedom of Channel 101
overview: One of the few appearances of who would seven years later become MainCharacter and SecondCharacter, as they present the benefits of R&M co-creator Dan Harmon's Channel 101, a short film festival in which you can have more freedom to express yourself than you can on television or even YouTube for that matter. You'll have to look up the original version for yourself if you want to see what I censored (it's not Doc's balls, YouTube haven't done anything about that in years)
